ASABA – The newly elected Captain of Ibori Golf and Country Club (IGCC), Asaba, Mr. Larry Osai has promised to attract national and international golfing tournament to the golf course in Delta State. Speaking at the Captain’s Inaugural tournament that ushered him in with his other executive members on Wednesday, he noted that uplifting the club to an enviable height in the global golfers’ arena was one of his executive members’ vision and they hope to achieve it within the shortest possible time. While noting his responsibility as Captain in ensuring the progress of the club, he stated that with concerted effort the goals would be achieved within a given period but prayed for the absolute cooperation of all members The captain acknowledged the contributions of his predecessors who started it and made it grow to the present level and he assured that the goal of putting IGCC in global Golf map will be achieved in this dispensation if all are committed to the vision. He assured that the door is open for ideas and opinion for the progress of the Club irrespective of positions. Likewise, Dr. Ifeanyi Osuoza said that Osai is a purposeful leader and able to carry people along in his drive to making the golf club worth the while. He promised to work with him to ensure he succeeds with fewer difficulties. Ogbueshi Peter Iweze who is known popularly for his Caddies Tournament, also acknowledged that Osai is very committed to anything that he does and would do more exploits in his tenure while assuring him of all needed support. A Captain of IBB Golf Club, Abuja, Senator Emmanuel Anosike said that IGCC, Asaba would get the support from his club as it is their custom to support any of their members. He noted that the new captain, Larry Osai is a member and his presence will attract attention from IBB Abuja.